		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				With eyes still red, either from the drink or some other cause, Lothannon scans the room. <br>  <br> Noting the newcomers with a weary gaze he moves to a table, not the same one as before, which by now has been cleared away, but to another closer to the hearth. <br>  <br> &quot;Lady Rakash&quot;  the knight bows once &quot;New friends, welcome.  I am Sir Lothannon Silverlight and have been resident here for some time now while the laggardly Innkeeper attempts to find me a remount so I can continue my journey.&quot; <br>  <br> Looking like a healer has just forced him to swallow a particularly vile concoction the knight continues, <br>  <br> &quot;It appears I may owe you all an apology for my unseemly behaviour.  I was hm..quite deranged ah and do sincerely apologise for any offence caused&quot; <br>  <br> After ordering a platter of something hot to eat from the Innkeeper the knight sits, waving away the profered jug, and gazes deep into the glowing embers of the fire. <br>  <br> 		

