		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Ah Lady Rakash I was, no doubt speaking of my ah...lost wife.  *A look of desolation enters his eyes, to be supressed with a visable effort* <br>  <br> I say lost, though she certainly knows exactly where she is.  Simply lost to me. <br>  <br> I suppose I ought to take some comfort in it being Tunare's will but may She forgive me, though at this point..... <br>  <br> *falls silent for a moment* <br>  <br> Of course I cannot recall saying such things, I must admit to my shame. <br>  <br> So Lady to answer thy concern she was my wife and now she is no longer.  And at this point I find myself wondering if she was ever my lover..... <br>  <br> *Looks deep into the heart of the fire as if to purge his own thoughts in their glowing depths*		

