			<td class="BoardRowA">12/17/99 8:37am</td>
			<td class="BoardRowA"><a name="19907"><span style="font-weight: bold;">
				*takes a sip of her drink as her eyes flame briefly at the knight*
			</span></a></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				And so the False Mothe, er, Tunare has taken her from you?  Is not Tunare often confused with Erollisi?  In my understanding, Tunare is the goddess of life and Erollisi the goddess of love. <br>  <br> Perhaps your quarrel is not with Tunare but with Erollisi?  Life is never intended to be easy and this love of which you speak is treacherous in nature. <br>  <br> *nods for a brief moment* <br>  <br> This so-called emotion of love is a strong poison.  I have seen it cause among the pale races more grief, more destruction than any wars in Norrathian history. I sometimes wonder if Homunculus' self-loathing is rooted in love somehow.  <br>  <br> *a brief shrug* <br>  <br> Why you pales subject yourselves to such a destructive force I shall never understand.  Perhaps the Teir'Dal way is better... we have no concept of love, and so no marriage, no jealousy or broken hearts.  We have no such reasons to fight among ourselves as your races do. <br>  <br> *takes another bite of hot roasted meats and dabs the corners of her mouth most daintily* <br>  <br> I do however understand a warmth of heart in attraction to another. And if such is like this love you choose to be enslaved to then I am sorry you choose to be in pain. <br>  <br> If you would like I would gladly cut short your slavery to love in this life and send you to your rest.  I have become quite skilled at a rather quick and relatively painless poisoned backstab... a mere prick along your spine and a glow of warmth through your body and then peace from your torment. <br>  <br> *a soft, almost merciful, smile on an indigo face as a hand reaches for a poisoned blade still in it's guard* <br>  <br> It's up to you, knight.		

