			<td class="BoardRowA"><a name="20778"><span style="font-weight: bold;">
				*something..big...lodges in the Tavern's doorway*
			</span></a></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				*The Dread Oak Portal of the Tavern creaks grudgingly aside, and heathlight can be seen coruscating across a burnished mass of Bronze beyond. It heaves and strains, attempting to attain egress to the inviting interior, then a sotto voce bassy muttering ensues. Gutrot enters, sidling crabways in his cumbersome armour and panoply of knapsacks, satchels and backpacks which rattle in percussion with his every movement* <br>  <br> Bluddee hell, dat fing get smaller or did Gutrot get bigger den? <br>  <br> *The Trollee, large even for a member of his species, hulks into the dim Common Area, shooting a glowering backwards look to the doorframe, then suspiciously around at the assembled patrons* <br>  <br> *broad grin* Hey up dere, Misturr Sir Lothannon, how'z it gowin' yur flower-sniffin' poetree reedin' Pally? Fansee a drink den do yur, Gutrot'z treet? *seems oblivious to the Knight's glumness* <br>  <br> *scans the room further, a split-melon grin slowly spreading across his face in obvious unconcealed delight at the presence of a pair of Big Brudders* <br>  <br> Wotcha, Brudders, how'z it hangin'? Nevvur seen annuver Trollee or Ogrim in 'ere beeforr, serpryzed dere eenuff room to akkomodayt uz all , har har har. <br>  <br> *finally spots Rakash, perched on a bench before the hearth, and amiably ambles over, subjecting her to a Megawatt beam* <br>  <br> *clonk-clonk of paraphernalia with every step* Rak, gud to see yur 'ere agayn! <br>  <br>  *envelops her in a warm, unstoppable hug before remembering himself and desisting the display of affection amongst the Lightdwellers* <br>  <br>  Har har, Gutrot meenz; Well met, fellow Kownsillur *slow wink of Kunnin' Trollee Guile* <br>  <br>  *spots the decimated plate of varying meats*  <br>  <br>  Yum, fankz for offerin', Gutrot iz famished.  <br>  <br> *Seats his wobbly green arse on the other end of the bench, almost catapulting Rakash to the far end of the room, then whisks the scraps away and upends the entire plate into his cavernous maw. After a moment, he eats the plate too with a thoughtful expression and much crunching of porcelain, unaware of the despairing look of the bartender behind him* <br>  <br> Yummee, dat hit der spot. Now, *speculative look* enneeewun need enneefing from der bar whilst Gutrot iz inna jenruss mood den? <br>  <br> *glances around with a snaggily grin at everyone, then back at Rakash who has arisen and is making a padding cat-like journey towards the stairwell* <br>  <br> Off upstairs, Rak? Gess yur do deservv a bit ov a brayk from aller dat Blakksmivvin' yur dowin'. Gutrot duzzent wanter see yur do yorself inter der grownd dere, wot? Let yor big green buddee know if dere'z enneefing yur need, okay. <br>  <br> Gutrot, <br> Ebon Kownsillur.		

